SIMPLE: newly
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Newly
<hw>New"ly</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lately;
recently.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He rubbed it o'er with <qex>newly</qex> gathered mint.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Anew; afresh; freshly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And the refined mind doth <qex>newly</qex> fashion⟦br⟧
Into a fairer form.</q> <rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>new-made</ent>⟦br⟧
